profileText: a Representative from Utah; born in Ogden, Utah, June 22, 1980; graduated from Ogden High School, Ogden, Utah, 1998; attended Utah State University, Logan, Utah; B.A., University of Utah, Salt Lake City, Utah; M.P.P.A., Northwestern University, Evanston, Ill., 2018; consultant; Foreign Service Officer, United States Department of State; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Seventeenth Congress (January 3, 2021–present).
